   "body" : "As we saw, Bitcoin is using a [test_framework](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/tree/master/test/functional/test_framework) of its own to testing thousands of cases. All the script files [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/tree/master/test/functional) are using `test_framework`.\r\n\r\nThe main question is: Why instead of use [unittest](https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html), a special custom test system was written from the beginning? Is there a goal or plan of migrating whole testing system to the `unittest`?\r\n\r\nThank you, just wondering... :)",
